definition: thick pole/bar/rod/thick line/to mark with a thick line/to sharpen (knife)/(old) coffin-bearing pole
tree/wood/coffin/wooden/simple/numb/one of the eight categories of ancient musical instruments 八音[ba1 yin1]
to bicker/to argue for the sake of arguing/to carry on poles (together with sb else)/to carry a coffin on poles
extortion by taking advantage of sb's weakness
to carry out gymnastic tricks on horizontal bar

sentences.english: Buy red eagle, cash straight drop 8000 yuan, add send whole car decoration poles.
sentences.chinese: 购瑞鹰，现金直降8000元，加送全车装饰杠。

sentences.english: In game nine, the bobbin bar mahjong two eight.
sentences.chinese: 合玩牌九，筒子杠麻将二八杠等。

sentences.english: Make the poles of acacia wood and overlay them with gold.
sentences.chinese: 要用皂荚木作杠，用金包裹。

sentences.english: The poles for carrying the table were made of acacia wood and were overlaid with gold.
sentences.chinese: 他用皂荚木做两根杠，用金包裹，以便抬桌子。

sentences.english: For their wings were outstretched over the place where the ark was, covering the ark and its rods.
sentences.chinese: 基路伯张著翅膀在约柜之上，遮掩约柜和抬柜的杠。

sentences.english: a over the molar volume squared.
sentences.chinese: 等于a除以摩尔体积V杠的平方。

sentences.english: Make poles of acacia wood for the altar and overlay them with bronze.
sentences.chinese: 又要为祭坛做杠，就是皂荚木的杠，要包上铜。

sentences.english: Make rods of the same wood, plated with gold, for lifting the table.
sentences.chinese: 要用皂荚木做两根杠，用金包裹，以便抬桌子。

sentences.english: They made the poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with bronze.
sentences.chinese: 用皂荚木做杠，用铜包裹。

sentences.english: And upon the golden altar they shall spread a cloth of blue, and cover it with a covering of badgers' skins, and shall put to the staves thereof
sentences.chinese: 在金坛上要铺蓝色毯子，蒙上海狗皮，把杠穿上。

sentences.english: You are just quarrelling, I don't want to continue the conversation.
sentences.chinese: 你完全是在和人顶杠，我不想和你继续说下去了。

sentences.english: They inserted the poles into the rings so they would be on the sides of the altar for carrying it.
sentences.chinese: 把杠穿在坛两旁的环子内，用以抬杠。

sentences.english: The cherubim spread their wings over the place of the ark and overshadowed the ark and its carrying poles.
sentences.chinese: 基路伯张着翅膀在约柜之上，遮掩约柜和抬柜的杠。
